M5 is only available for &quot;my&quot; setting, so only for you hitting something <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uiboozer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>iboozer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/20/02 3:30:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22895.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Not quite done right, I think...</span><hr size=1> Well I messed with it and I don't like either. It's nice to have all the battle spam out of the chat window, but a MUCH better option would have been to just make another &quot;chat window&quot; that is only used for battle messages, and the normal chat window would be for the rest. This battle spam chat window should be just like the normal chat window, scrollable, moveable, resizeable, so that I could basically just stack the 2 chat windows.<br>
<br>
I don't like the fact that your hits, mob hitting you, and mob missing you can't be in the same window. Made it hard to tell whats going on in a way, because there is no time relation to things. Also you dodging, riposting, etc. still shows in the main chat window... poor implementation. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=46099">iboozer</a> - 54 Rogue of Bristlebane<BR>&lt;Legion of Obsidian Knights&gt;<BR>/tell me on Veeshan anytime!</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uiboozer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>iboozer</A> at: 3/20/02 9:48:59 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uloral.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Loral</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/20/02 8:37:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22895.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://loralciriclight.com/images/loral_face_60x60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Not quite done right, I think...</span><hr size=1> I stuck mine over on the left side of the screen using positions 10 by 500 (on a 1600 by 1200 window).  I use the 0 for background graphics and headers and mode 4 so it only appears as a number.  As a cleric, I want to know how much I hit for and when I am getting hit, but not to get in the way of group and raid channels =)<br>
<br>
I think this is how it came out:<br>
<br>
/hitsmode my m5 10 400 5 1 0 0 20<br>
<br>
/hitsmode me m5 10 500 5 1 0 0 20<br>
<br>
This worked well for me. <p><a href="http://loralciriclight.com/"><img src="http://loralciriclight.com/images/loral_dragon_sig.jpg" border="0" alt="Loral's Signature" height="132" width="302"></a>
<br />
<a href="http://loralciriclight.com/loral.html">bio</a> - <a href="http://loralciriclight.com/">stories</a> - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=16545">equip</a> - <a href="http://loralciriclight.com/images/">screenshots</a> - <a href="http://loralciriclight.com/refdesk.html">eq links</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucelarastarshine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Celara Starshine</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_2.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/20/02 9:23:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22895.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://eroara.homestead.com/files/cel.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Not quite done right, I think...</span><hr size=1> I used it so that I can turn on others hits on my enchanter and see who is breaking my mezes.  Since I now have hits on it will be logged, but not spamming my normal chat window... I can either quickly look up and see who is breaking mez or check my log.<br>
<br>
I will propably keep it this way for my rogue too. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubearberry.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bearberry</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/20/02 9:28:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22895.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Not quite done right, I think...</span><hr size=1> /agree Onodrim &amp; Iboozer<br>
