I don't want my melee spam spread across 3 different windows, I want it all in one window and everything else in the other. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unocte.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nocte</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.gifs.net/animate/danger01.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/20/02 10:01:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22895.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.fortunecity.com/nocte1/Sig/SigPhot.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Not quite done right, I think...</span><hr size=1> I am sure this will be implemented into the "New-Improved-Vastly-Superior" interface whenever they get around to releasing it. However- having the ability to access and manipulate this stuff from the command line is nice for hot key macros. You can swap your settings on the fly if you use transparent backgrounds and and need to toggle the background to opaque in "bright" areas. <br>
