<br>
It's a great idea, and it can definitely be improved upon; but right now in its present state, it's not overly useful.  But I think if they would rethink it a bit and work on making it more friendly, it would be a great asset.<br>
<br>
I agree with the person who said that they are a little lazy when it comes to stuff like this, expecting the community of users to do their work for them.  <br>
<br>
I've often wondered why VI hasn't hard-coded sound triggers when spells are about to drop, or when you get a tell, etc.  and make those things customizable, in case you don't like the sounds associated with those things.  Then I found out that there's already a 3rd party program out there that does this, so why would they bother?  They should...do you know how many times I've died from &quot;you are drowning&quot; in Kedge because I was too caught up in the battle?  More than I want to admit.  Could've easily been avoided if, when the spell started blinking, a sound was triggered letting me know that it's time to recast EB...oh well, just an example of another way that EQ could be improved without third party help.  <br>
<br>
Likely, the weight of improving this feature will fall on the backs of the users who have the know-how (which isn't me, hehe); so give it some time, maybe someone will come up with something. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uveenublue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>veenublue</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/20/02 11:15:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22895.topic&index=31>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.phank.com/avitars/smallavitar.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> here is my set up</span><hr size=1> Here is a link to a grided pict of my interface with the new info on it:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.phank.com/images/misc/newstuff">www.phank.com/images/misc/newstuff</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
The grid is about 100x100 in the game world. So here is what I typed:<br>
<br>
for others hits:<br>
/hitsmode other m3 500 0 3 0 0<br>
<br>
for my hits:<br>
/hitsmode my m4 620 60 6 0 0<br>
<br>
for me getting hit:<br>
/hitsmode me m4 620 100 6 0 0<br>
<br>
m3 = some discription<br>
m4 = only numbers<br>
<br>
